Visualize ExG, orientation and spectral analysis data in real-time by navigating to the Visualization page.

You can configure the visualization via the drop-down menus at the top of the Visualization page or by selecting ‘Filters’.

<figure style="text-align:center;">
<img class="mobile" src="/img/Desktop/settings.PNG" alt="The visualization settings of Explore Desktop" width="90%"/>
<figcaption> Use the settings at the top of Visualization page to configure your visualization. </figcaption>
</figure>

Settings include:
- Signal – EEG or ECG mode.
	- EEG provides the spectral analysis plot of the signal. ECG mode detects heartbeats and calculates heart rate from the RR-intervals.
- Y-axis scale – change the range of the y-axis.
	- 1 uV to 100 mV range.
- Time window – change the time interval of the x-axis.
	- 5, 10, or 20 second range.
- Heart rate – if in ECG mode, heart rates will be computed and displayed.
- Record (see Recording Section).
- Event markers (see Event Markers).
- Filters.

