## Filters
The Visualization page will prompt you to define your visualization filters. Explore Desktop will begin streaming data once you have selected your filters.

<figure style="float:right;">
<img class="mobile" src="/img/Desktop/vissettings.PNG" alt="The visualization filters of Explore Desktop" width="350"/>
<figcaption> Set the visualization filters using the pop-up. </figcaption>
</figure>

You will still be able to filter signals while the device is streaming. To do so, select ‘Filters’.

The following filters are available:
- Baseline correction – removes the signal’s DC offset, based on previous signal values.
- Notch filter (band stop filter) – rejects signals that fall outside some frequency band.
- Low cutoff frequency – rejects signals with frequencies below some threshold.
- High cutoff frequency – rejects signals with frequencies above some threshold.


